item.title: Post-OPEC+ Oil Rally Fades as Investor Sentiment Remains Weak
item.description: Oil prices were more than 1% lower in Europe, unwinding all their gains following Sunday’s OPEC+ meeting, as inventors focus on worries about the global economy.

item.title: Metal Prices Mixed Amid Uncertain Macroenvironment
item.description: Base metals prices were mixed, while gold edged higher, with ANZ pointing to subdued demand and lower inventories protecting against downside risks.

item.title: Ten-Year Bund Yield at 2.4% Seen as Level for Tactical Longs
item.description: Commerzbank Research recommends investors tactical longs at yield levels of 2.4% for the 10-year German Bund.

item.title: Major Dam Blown Up in Russian-Occupied Ukraine
item.description: Russia and Ukraine blamed each other for the destruction of the dam and power plant as thousands face imminent flooding on both sides of the front line.

item.title: Dollar Falls as Weak US ISM Data Dampens Fed Rate-Rise Prospects
item.description: The dollar edged lower as Monday’s unexpectedly weak ISM services activity data raised concerns about the U.S. economy, which could hinder further interest-rate increases.

item.title: German Manufacturing Orders Unexpectedly Drop
item.description: New orders at German factories fell 0.4% in April on month, against expectations of a 3% rise, signalling continued declining demand in the country’s key manufacturing sector particularly for foreign orders.

item.title: UK Retail Sales Growth Slows to 6-Month Low
item.description: Retail sales in the U.K. for the four weeks to May 27 increased by 3.9%, below the three-month average and despite the three bank holidays.

item.title: British American Tobacco Keeps Outlook
item.description: British American Tobacco reiterated its 2023 guidance for revenue and earnings growth, and backed its existing strategy.

item.title: Nikkei Rises 0.9% to New 33-Year High, Led by Trading Houses
item.description: Japanese stocks ended higher, led by gains in trading houses and steelmakers, as brightened U.S. economic outlook added to the local market’s recent rising momentum.

item.title: RBA Announces Further Rate Increase, Sees More on Horizon
item.description: The Reserve Bank of Australia announced its 12th rise in interest rates in just over a year, and warned that if inflation remains problematic, further increases are likely.

item.title: India Train Crash Rescuers Describe Search of Railcars Filled With Bodies
item.description: The country’s top disaster-response force had to cut through metal and search railcars filled with bodies after the three-way crash that killed at least 275 people.

item.title: Ukraine Launched Biggest Attacks in Months, Moscow Says
item.description: Moscow said it had fended off the largest Ukrainian assault in months in eastern Ukraine as Kyiv moved to retake the initiative in the 15-month war.

item.title: Apple's Augmented Reality Faces Real Questions
item.description: The Vision Pro headset is an expensive gamble for a company that needs a new hit.

item.title: A former executive at TikTok's parent company alleges in a legal filing that a committee of China's Communist Party members accessed the data of the app's users in Hong Kong in 2018, a contention the company denies.
